misconceptions.inferred_category_name: No detectable notional-machine misconception (correct parallel-array sort and selection)
misconceptions.student_thought_process: The student believes that if they swap scores during sorting, they must also swap the corresponding names at the same indices so the two arrays stay aligned, and that after sorting ascending the top student will be at index n-1.
misconceptions.conceptual_gap: No gap found. This matches Java’s execution model: arrays are indexed containers, swaps mutate array contents, and bubble sort with synchronized swaps keeps parallel arrays consistent. After an ascending sort, the maximum score is at the last index.
misconceptions.error_manifestation: None for valid inputs (N>0 with N names and N integer scores). Produces correct output for the sample and the stated requirements.
